ds%20and%20152.1%20pounds%20for%20women%2C%20per%20the%20Korean%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weighing%20will%20take%20place%20in%20front%20of%20the%20gates%20and%20before%20boarding%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.koreatimes.co.kr%2Fwww%2Ftech%2F2023%2F08%2F129_357431.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Korea%20Times%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20an%20online%20backlash%20to%20the%20measure%2C%20with%20some%20potential%20passengers%20raising%20concerns%20about%20their%20privacy%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Korea%20JoongAng%20Daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20airline%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20passengers%20who%20feel%20uncomfortable%20with%20the%20process%20can%20communicate%20their%20feelings%20to%20boarding%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETravel%20industry%20experts%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairline-check-ins-weight-watchers-scenario-customers-says-experts-2021-6%5C%22%3EInsider%20in%20June%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20US%20airlines%20are%20unlikely%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20with%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Authority%20currently%20allowing%20operators%20to%20ask%20passengers%20to%20volunteer%20their%20weight%20and%20%26quot%3Bmake%20a%20reasonable%20estimate%26quot%3B%20if%20the%20answer%20appears%20too%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20New%20Zealand%2C%20however%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-new-zealand-weigh-passengers-before-boarding-2023-5%5C%22%3Easking%20passengers%20to%20step%20on%20the%20scale%3C%2Fa%3Es%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpassenger%20weight%20survey%26quot%3B%20to%20fulfill%20a%20requirement%20by%20New%20Zealand's%20Civil%20Aviation%20Authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-korea-airline-weigh-passengers-scales-boarding-gates-before-flights-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A16927970500