ints%20taken.%20He%20traveled%20to%20the%2015th%20floor%20of%20the%20same%20building%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbooking-trump-no-cuffs-no-mugshot-shortest-perp-walk-2023-4%5C%22%3Ewas%20perp-walked%20for%20just%20five%20feet%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20front%20of%20press%20cameras%2C%20going%20straight%20from%20the%20DA's%20private%20corridor%20to%20the%20courtroom.%20In%20the%20courtroom%2C%20he%20had%20a%20combined%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-arraignment-pleads-not-guilty-new-york-indictment-2023-4%5C%22%3Einitial%20appearance%20and%20arraignment%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20a%20judge%2C%20where%20he%20pleaded%20not%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20process%20took%20about%20two%20hours.%20Trump%20had%20time%20to%20make%20it%20back%20home%20to%20Mar-a-Lago%20for%20dinner%20and%20a%20speech%20in%20front%20of%20his%20supporters%20that%20same%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Atlanta%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-georgia-grand-jury-fulton-county-fani-willis-2023-8%5C%22%3Ethe%20Fulton%20County%20district%20attorney%20charged%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20array%20of%20crimes%20for%20trying%20to%20overturn%20Georgia's%202020%20election%20results%2C%20that%20same%20process%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20several%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20offense%2C%20but%20that's%20way%20too%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20'lightning%20speed'%20for%20Atlanta%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20said%20he'll%20go%20to%20Atlanta%20on%20Thursday%20where%20he'll%20be%20booked%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-and-co-defendants-will-booked-at-notorious-atlanta-jail-2023-8%5C%22%3Ethe%20Fulton%20County%20jail%2C%20known%20locally%20as%20Rice%20Street%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%2013%20charges%20ranging%20from%20RICO%20%E2%80%94%20a%20racketeering%20charge%20%E2%80%94%20to%20illegally%20pressuring%20public%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Labat%2C%20the%20sheriff%20who%20oversees%20the%20jail%2C%20said%20he%20plans%20to%20follow%20%26quot%3Bnormal%20practices%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwe-have-mugshots-ready-fulton-county-georgia-sheriff-trump-indictment-2023-8%5C%22%3Etake%20the%20mugshots%20and%20fingerprints%20of%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20his%2018%20co-defendants%2C%20who%20have%20until%20August%2025%20to%20voluntarily%20show%20up%20for%20booking.%20Trump%20can%20skip%20the%20initial%20appearance%20%E2%80%94%20which%20often%20happens%20before%20a%20magistrate%20judge%20in%20the%20jail%20building%20%E2%80%94%20because%20his%20lawyers%20already%20secured%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-cash-bond-georgia-rico-case-2023-8%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20%24200%2C000%20bond%20package%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFulton%20County%20District%20Attorney%20Fani%20Willis%20has%20said%20she%20wants%20to%20hold%20an%20arraignment%20%E2%80%94%20where%20defendants%20are%20formally%20presented%20with%20the%20charges%20and%20enter%20a%20plea%20before%20a%20Superior%20Court%20judge%20%E2%80%94%20with%20all%20of%20the%20defendants%20on%20the%20week%20of%20September%205.%20It%20might%20be%20held%20over%20Zoom%20instead%20of%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20states%2C%20including%20New%20York%2C%20have%20what's%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bunitary%20process%26quot%3B%20that%2C%20under%20certain%20conditions%2C%20allow%20a%20booking%2C%20initial%20appearance%2C%20and%20arraignment%20to%20all%20happen%20at%20about%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFulton%20County%20doesn't%20have%20that.%20Bookings%20%26quot%3Bnever%26quot%3B%20happen%20in%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%2C%20which%20is%20down%20the%20street%20from%20the%20Superior%20Court%20where%20arraignments%20take%20place%2C%20former%20DeKalb%20County%20District%20Attorney%20J.Tom%20Morgan%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20arraignment%20to%20take%20place%20within%20two%20weeks%20from%20the%20arrest%2C%20it's%20lightning%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20Morgan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bextraordinarily%20fast%26quot%3B%20arraignment%20is%20possible%20because%20Willis%20has%20already%20brought%20a%20grand%20jury%20indictment%20against%20Trump%20and%20the%20other%20defendants%2C%20according%20to%20Morgan%2C%20who%20is%20now%20a%20criminal%20law%20professor%20at%20Western%20Carolina%20University.%20Other%20cases%20take%20much%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20people%20don't%20have%20attorneys%20on%20the%20day%20they're%20arrested%2C%26quot%3B%20Morgan%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20arraignment%20cannot%20happen%20without%20formal%20charges.%20Formal%20charges%20usually%20take%20weeks%2C%20sometimes%20months%20for%20the%20DA%20to%20present.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224982%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%20Manhattan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F642c90dfd335200018dda74d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20U.S.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20arrives%20at%20Manhattan%20Criminal%20Courthouse%2C%20after%20his%20indictment%20by%20a%20Manhattan%20grand%20jury%20in%20New%20York%20City%20%E2%80%94%20the%20greatest%20city%20in%20the%20world.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FBrendan%20McDermid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20process%20is%20not%20particularly%20efficient.%20There%20are%20a%20number%20of%20reasons%20why%20the%20Manhattan%20and%20Fulton%20County%20criminal%20justice%20systems%20are%20handling%20these%20events%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Manhattan%20district%20attorney's%20office%2C%20New%20York%20Police%20Department%2C%20state%20court%20security%20system%2C%20US%20Secret%20Service%2C%20and%20other%20city%20authorities%20painstakingly%20choreographed%20Trump's%20court%20appearance%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20the%20case%20in%20Atlanta.%20At%20least%20publicly%2C%20the%20sheriff's%20office%20is%20handling%20booking%20no%20differently%20than%20it%20would%20with%20anyone%20else%20charged%20with%20a%20crime.%20The%20district%20attorney's%20office%20hasn't%20made%20any%20special%20arrangements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%2019%20co-defendants%20in%20the%20alleged%20election%20interference%20scheme%20are%20showing%20up%20to%20jail%20at%20different%20times%2C%20Willis%20has%20said%20she%20wants%20to%20arraign%20everyone%20in%20one%20shot.%20Spacing%20out%20the%20bookings%20and%20arraignments%20lets%20her%20and%20the%20court%20get%20their%20ducks%20in%20a%20row%20before%20an%20arraignment%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20does%20ensure%20that%20those%20who%20are%20to%20be%20arraigned%20have%20completed%20the%20prior%20processes%20and%20done%20it%20on%20schedule%2C%26quot%3B%20Ronald%20L.%20Carlson%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20there's%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20housekeeping.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20one%20other%20reason%20Manhattan%20did%20it%20better%2C%20which%20is%20that%20Atlanta%20is%20not%20a%20perp-walkable%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City%2C%20and%20particularly%20Manhattan%2C%20is%20famously%20walkable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EManhattan%20is%20better%20than%20Atlanta%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20in%20the%20city%20and%20I%20do%20not%20own%20a%20car%2C%20nor%20do%20I%20need%20one%20for%20my%20daily%20life%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20many%20factors%20that%20make%20New%20York%20the%20best%20city%20in%20America%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20things%20like%20good%20pizza%2C%20the%20Metropolitan%20Museum%20of%20Art%2C%20and%20occasionally%20seeing%20Steve%20Buscemi%20on%20the%20subway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York's%20court%20system%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20this%20great%20efficiency.%20In%20April%2C%20Trump%20traveled%20to%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%20from%20Trump%20Tower%20with%20his%20motorcade%2C%20but%20he%20could%20have%20taken%20a%2028-minute%20subway%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20took%20the%20elevator%20to%20the%20courtroom%20for%20his%20arraignment.%20If%20he%20wanted%20to%20check%20out%20the%20building%20where%20the%20grand%20jury%20indicted%20him%2C%20he%20could%20have%20walked%20across%20the%20street.%20To%20see%20the%20protests%20and%20counterprotests%20over%20his%20indictment%2C%20he%20could%20have%20looked%20out%20the%20window%20to%20Collect%20Pond%20Park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20could%20have%20turned%20left%20on%20the%20sidewalk%20and%20walked%20a%20few%20buildings%20over%20to%20a%20federal%20courthouse%20to%20attend%20his%20civil%20sexual%20abuse%20trial%20later%20that%20month%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-liable-rape-e-jean-carroll-jury-verdict-2023-5%5C%22%3Ehe%20lost%20to%20E.%20Jean%20Carroll%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Trump%20never%20attended%20the%20trial%2C%20a%20possible%20factor%20in%20his%20loss).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20trial%2C%20he%20could%20have%20gone%20two%20flights%20up%20in%20the%20same%20building%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fed-sheeran-strums-guitar-sings-lets-get-it-on-trial-2023-4%5C%22%3Ewatch%20a%20musical%20performance%20from%20Ed%20Sheeran%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20copyright%20lawsuit%20he%20ultimately%20won.%20Around%20the%20corner%20from%20that%20building%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftimeline-jeffrey-epstein-final-days-manhattan-jail-investigation-2023-6%5C%22%3Ethe%20jail%20where%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%20killed%20himself%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20that%20rich%20history%20is%20a%2014-minute%20walk%20from%20Insider's%20office%2C%20which%20is%20very%20good%20for%20me%2C%20a%20reporter%20who%20covers%20court%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtlanta%20is%20a%20mess%20by%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20being%20booked%20in%20the%20same%20building%20at%20the%20courthouse%2C%20Trump%20will%20be%20booked%20at%20the%20Rice%20Street%20jail%20which%2C%20according%20to%20Google%20Maps%2C%20is%20a%2092-minute%20walk%20from%20Fulton%20County%20Superior%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22rice%20street%20jail%20fulton%20county%20atlanta%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e50814912f290019a8fd56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFulton%20County%20Sheriffs%20install%20barricades%20outside%20the%20Fulton%20County%20Jail%2C%20making%20it%20even%20less%20walkable.%20LOL%20%40%20those%20%26quot%3Bsidewalks.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECHANDAN%20KHANNA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20streets%20are%20hardly%20conducive%20to%20walking%20either%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20highway-like%20stretches%20that%20could%20result%20in%20a%20criminal%20defendant%20getting%20hit%20by%20a%20car%2C%20on%20top%20of%20all%20their%20other%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%2C%20county%20court%2C%20and%20federal%20court%20are%20all%20nearby%20each%20other%20in%20downtown%20Atlanta.%20But%20overall%2C%20the%20streets%20are%20not%20walkable.%20You%20cannot%20have%20a%20good%20perp-walk%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20walkability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20get%20me%20wrong.%20There%20are%20plenty%20of%20problems%20with%20New%20York%20City's%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERikers%20Island%2C%20where%20incarcerated%20defendants%20pending%20trial%20in%20Manhattan%20state%20court%20are%20held%2C%20is%20surrounded%20by%20water%20and%20therefore%20not%20walkable.%20Criminal%20defense%20lawyers%20often%20complain%20about%20difficulties%20getting%20access%20to%20their%20defendants%20and%20preparing%20for%20trial%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Farticle%2Frikers-deaths-jail.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20other%20issues%20with%20Rikers%20that%20are%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20this%20hot%20take%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20problems%20are%20not%20dissimilar%20from%20Fulton%20County's%20jail%2C%20which%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-and-co-defendants-will-booked-at-notorious-atlanta-jail-2023-8%5C%22%3Eplagued%20by%20horrific%20inmate%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20federal%20level%20in%20New%20York%2C%20there%20is%20the%20aforementioned%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%20suicide%20and%20a%20host%20of%20other%20problems%20that%20led%20to%20the%20Manhattan%20federal%20jail's%20closure%2C%20which%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-limited-peanut-butter-jelly-sandwiches-jail-2023-8%5C%22%3Edefendants%20have%20been%20held%20across%20the%20river%20in%20Brooklyn%20instead%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20you%20sometimes%20even%20come%20across%20Ed%20Sheeran%20singing%20%E2%80%94%20rarely%20a%20pleasant%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20for%20both%20Atlanta%20and%20Manhattan%20is%20more%20urban%20density.%20Build%20more%20buildings%2C%20closer%20together%2C%20to%20speed%20things%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtlanta%20also%20ought%20to%20think%20about%20scheduling%20arraignments%20and%20bookings%20to%20happen%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20in%20a%20location%20clustered%20together.%20If%20defendants%20like%20Trump%20have%20already%20made%20bond%20arrangements%20that%20don't%20require%20them%20to%20be%20jailed%2C%20there's%20no%20point%20in%20taking%20them%20to%20a%20jail%20an%20hour-and-a-half's%20trek%20from%20the%20walkable%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-atlanta-rico-booking-arraignment-new-york-perp-walkable-cities-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692788401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22